Neighbor Discovery for blip
In IPv6, neighbor discovery resolves IPv6 addresses which have been determined to be on-link to their associated link-layer addresses. This simple component follows the advice of 6lowpan-nd, which states that link-local addresses are derived from the associated link-layer addressed deterministically. Therefore, we can do a very simple translation between the two types of addresses.
In the future, implementors could consider adding more complicated address resolution mechanisms here.
